cs.CL, cs.FL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and grammar.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses connections between Sequential Constraint Grammar and formal language theory.
- cs.LG (Learning) is a possible category as the paper proposes resource bounds that restrict the generative power of SCG to a subset of context sensitive languages.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the undecidability of Nonmonotonic SCG.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of implementing SCG with a Turing machine.
